cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper describes a neural network weight compression approach using a learned probability model and entropy penalty during training. This method is evaluated on classification benchmarks, indicating a focus on machine learning and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a latent space and reparameterization suggests a focus on deep learning (cs.LG) and the use of a probability model suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of arithmetic coding for compression suggests a focus on information theory (cs.IT) or multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of hyperparameters suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
